# Dokploy Configuration
# Replace 'your-github-username' in docker-compose.yml with your actual GitHub username
# 
# Setup steps:
# 1. Push this repo to GitHub
# 2. GitHub Actions will build and push image to ghcr.io/your-github-username/gym-book-fe
# 3. In Dokploy, add this docker-compose.yml as a new application
# 4. Update the image name with your GitHub username
# 5. Deploy

# GitHub Container Registry is public by default
# Make sure your GitHub account has packages enabled

# To pull from private registry in Dokploy:
# - Add Docker Hub / GHCR credentials in Dokploy settings
# - Or push to a private GHCR repo and configure registry auth
